#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "The &lt;body&gt; tags"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We introduced a lot of new tags in the previous section -- here's what you need\n"
"to know. The <c>&lt;p&gt;</c> (paragraph), <c>&lt;pre&gt;</c> (code block),\n"
"<c>&lt;note&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;warn&gt;</c> (warning) and <c>&lt;impo&gt;</c>\n"
"(important) tags all can contain one or more lines of text. Besides the\n"
"<c>&lt;table&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ul&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ol&gt;</c> and\n"
"<c>&lt;dl&gt;</c> elements (which we'll cover in just a bit), these are the\n"
"only tags that should appear immediately inside a <c>&lt;body&gt;</c> element.\n"
"Another thing -- these tags <e>should not</e> be stacked -- in other words,\n"
"don't put a <c>&lt;note&gt;</c> element inside a <c>&lt;p&gt;</c> element. As\n"
"you might guess, the <c>&lt;pre&gt;</c> element preserves its whitespace\n"
"exactly, making it well-suited for code excerpts.  You must name the\n"
"<c>&lt;pre&gt;</c> tag with a <c>caption</c> attribute:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:326
#, no-wrap
msgid "Named &lt;pre&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:327
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;pre caption=\"Output of uptime\"&gt;\n"
"# &lt;i&gt;uptime&lt;/i&gt;\n"
"16:50:47 up 164 days,  2:06,  5 users,  load average: 0.23, 0.20, 0.25\n"
"&lt;/pre&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

