#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "&lt;mail&gt; and &lt;uri&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:488
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We've taken a look at the <c>&lt;mail&gt;</c> tag earlier; it's used to link\n"
"some text with a particular email address, and takes the form <c>&lt;mail\n"
"link=\"foo.bar@example.com\"&gt;Mr. Foo Bar&lt;/mail&gt;</c>. If you want to display the\n"
"email address, you can use <c>&lt;mail&gt;foo.bar@example.com&lt;/mail&gt;</c>, this\n"
"would be displayed as <mail>foo.bar@example.com</mail>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:496
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Shorter forms make it easier to use names and emails of Gentoo developers. Both\n"
"<c>&lt;mail&gt;neysx&lt;/mail&gt;</c> and <c>&lt;mail link=\"neysx\"/&gt;</c>\n"
"would appear as <mail>neysx</mail>. If you want to use a Gentoo dev's email\n"
"with a different content than his full name, use the second form with some\n"
"content. For instance, use a dev's first name: <c>&lt;mail\n"
"link=\"neysx\"&gt;Xavier&lt;/mail&gt;</c> appears as <mail\n"
"link=\"neysx\">Xavier</mail>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:504
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is particularly useful when you want to name a developer whose name\n"
"contains \"funny\" characters that you can't type.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:509
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>&lt;uri&gt;</c> tag is used to point to files/locations on the Internet.\n"
"It has two forms -- the first can be used when you want to have the actual URI\n"
"displayed in the body text, such as this link to\n"
"<uri>http://forums.gentoo.org/</uri>.  To create this link, I typed\n"
"<c>&lt;uri&gt;http://forums.gentoo.org/&lt;/uri&gt;</c>.  The alternate form is\n"
"when you want to associate a URI with some other text -- for example, <uri\n"
"link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org/\">the Gentoo Forums</uri>.  To create\n"
"<e>this</e> link, I typed <c>&lt;uri link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org/\"&gt;the\n"
"Gentoo Forums&lt;/uri&gt;</c>. You don't need to write\n"
"<c>http://www.gentoo.org/</c> to link to other parts of the Gentoo web site.\n"
"For instance, a link to the <uri link=\"/doc/en/\">documentation main index</uri>\n"
"should be simply <c>&lt;uri link=\"/doc/en/index.xml\"&gt;documentation main\n"
"index&lt;/uri&gt;</c>. You can even omit <c>index.xml</c> when you link to a\n"
"directory index, e.g. <c>&lt;uri link=\"/doc/en/\"&gt;documentation main\n"
"index&lt;/uri&gt;</c>. Leaving the trailing slash saves an extra HTTP request.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:527
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should not use a <c>&lt;uri&gt;</c> tag with a <c>link</c> attribute that\n"
"starts with <c>mailto:</c>. In this case, use a <c>&lt;mail&gt;</c> tag.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:532
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Please avoid the <uri link=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Click_here\">click here\n"
"syndrome</uri> as recommended by the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.w3.org/QA/Tips/noClickHere\">W3C</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:540
#, no-wrap
msgid "Figures"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:544
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Here's how to insert a figure into a document -- <c>&lt;figure\n"
"link=\"mygfx.png\" short=\"my picture\" caption=\"my favorite picture of all\n"
"time\"/&gt;</c>.  The <c>link</c> attribute points to the actual graphic image,\n"
"the <c>short</c> attribute specifies a short description (currently used for\n"
"the image's HTML <c>alt</c> attribute), and a caption.  Not too difficult\n"
":)  We also support the standard HTML-style &lt;img src=\"foo.gif\"/&gt; tag\n"
"for adding images without captions, borders, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:556
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tables"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:560
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"GuideXML supports a simplified table syntax similar to that of HTML. To start a\n"
"table, use a <c>&lt;table&gt;</c> tag. Start a row with a <c>&lt;tr&gt;</c>\n"
"tag. However, for inserting actual table data, we <e>don't</e> support the HTML\n"
"&lt;td&gt; tag; instead, use the <c>&lt;th&gt;</c> if you are inserting a\n"
"header, and <c>&lt;ti&gt;</c> if you are inserting a normal informational\n"
"block. You can use a <c>&lt;th&gt;</c> anywhere you can use a <c>&lt;ti&gt;</c>\n"
"-- there's no requirement that <c>&lt;th&gt;</c> elements appear only in the\n"
"first row.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:571
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Besides, both table headers (<c>&lt;th&gt;</c>) and table items\n"
"(<c>&lt;ti&gt;</c>) accept the <c>colspan</c> and <c>rowspan</c> attributes to\n"
"span their content across rows, columns or both.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:577
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Furthermore, table cells (<c>&lt;ti&gt;</c> &amp; <c>&lt;th&gt;</c>) can be\n"
"right-aligned, left-aligned or centered with the <c>align</c> attribute.\n"
msgstr ""

