#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>oldbook</b> is used on old handbooks to indicate they are not maintained\n"
"    anymore\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:730
#, no-wrap
msgid "<b>obsolete</b> is used to mark a document as obsolete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:734
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When marking a document as obsolete, you might want to add a link to a new\n"
"version. The <c>redirect</c> attribute does just that. The user might be\n"
"automatically redirected to the new page but you should not rely on that\n"
"behaviour.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:740
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disclaimer sample"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:741
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE guide SYSTEM \"/dtd/guide.dtd\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;!-- &#36;Header&#36; --&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;guide disclaimer=\"obsolete\" redirect=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;title>Gentoo x86 Installation Guide&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;author title=\"Author\"&gt;\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:755
#, no-wrap
msgid "FAQs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:759
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"FAQ documents need to start with a list of questions with links to their\n"
"answers. Creating such a list is both time-consuming and error-prone. The list\n"
"can be created automatically if you use a <c>faqindex</c> element as the first\n"
"chapter of your document. This element has the same structure as a\n"
"<c>chapter</c> to allow some introductory text. The structure of the document\n"
"is expected to be split into chapters (at least one chapter) containing\n"
"sections, each section containing one question specified in its <c>title</c>\n"
"element with the answer in its <c>body</c>. The FAQ index will appear as one\n"
"section per chapter and one link per question.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:771
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A quick look at a <uri link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml\">FAQ</uri> and <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml?passthru=1\">its source</uri> should make the above\n"
"obvious.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:781
#, no-wrap
msgid "Handbook Format"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:783
#, no-wrap
msgid "Guide vs Book"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:787
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For high-volume documentation, such as the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1\">Installation Instructions</uri>, a\n"
"broader format was needed. We designed a GuideXML-compatible enhancement that\n"
"allows us to write modular and multi-page documentation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:796
#, no-wrap
msgid "Main File"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:800
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The first change is the need for a \"master\" document. This document contains no\n"
"real content, but links to the individual documentation modules. The syntax\n"
"doesn't differ much from GuideXML:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:805
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example book usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:806
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE book SYSTEM \"/dtd/book.dtd\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;!-- &#36;Header&#36; --&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;<i>book</i>&gt;\n"
"&lt;title&gt;Example Book Usage&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;author...&gt;\n"
"  ...\n"
"&lt;/author&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;abstract&gt;\n"
"  ...\n"
"&lt;/abstract&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;!-- The content of this document is licensed under the CC-BY-SA license --&gt;\n"
"&lt;!-- See http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0 --&gt;\n"
"&lt;license version=\"3.0\"/&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;version&gt;...&lt;/version&gt;\n"
"&lt;date&gt;...&lt;/date&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:830
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"So far no real differences (except for the <c>&lt;book&gt;</c> instead of\n"
"<c>&lt;guide&gt;</c> tag). Instead of starting with the individual\n"
"<c>&lt;chapter&gt;</c>s, you define a <c>&lt;part&gt;</c>, which is the\n"
"equivalent of a separate part in a book:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:836
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defining a part"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:837
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;part&gt;\n"
"&lt;title&gt;Part One&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"&lt;abstract&gt;\n"
"  ...\n"
"&lt;/abstract&gt;\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Defining the several chapters)</comment>\n"
"&lt;/part&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:848
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each part is accompanied by a <c>&lt;title&gt;</c> and an \n"
"<c>&lt;abstract&gt;</c> which gives a small introduction to the part.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:853
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside each part, you define the individual <c>&lt;chapter&gt;</c>s. Each\n"
"chapter <e>must</e> be a separate document. As a result it is no surprise that\n"
"a special tag (<c>&lt;include&gt;</c>) is added to allow including the separate\n"
"document.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:859
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defining a chapter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:860
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;chapter&gt;\n"
"&lt;title&gt;Chapter One&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"\n"
"  &lt;include href=\"path/to/chapter-one.xml\"/&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;/chapter&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:871
#, no-wrap
msgid "Designing the Individual Chapters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:875
#, no-wrap
msgid "The content of an individual chapter is structured as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:878
#, no-wrap
msgid "Chapter Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:879
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE sections SYSTEM \"/dtd/book.dtd\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;!-- &#36;Header&#36; --&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;!--  The content of this document is licensed under the CC-BY-SA license --&gt;\n"
"&lt;!--  See http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0 --&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;sections&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;abstract&gt;\n"
"  This is a small explanation on chapter one.\n"
"&lt;/abstract&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;version&gt;...&lt;/version&gt;\n"
"&lt;date&gt;...&lt;/date&gt;\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Define the several &lt;section&gt; and &lt;subsection&gt;)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"&lt;/sections&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:901
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside each chapter you can define <c>&lt;section&gt;</c>s (equivalent of\n"
"<c>&lt;chapter&gt;</c> in a Guide) and <c>&lt;subsection&gt;</c>s (equivalent\n"
"of <c>&lt;section&gt;</c> in a Guide).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:907
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each individual chapter should have its own date and version elements. The\n"
"latest date of all chapters and master document will be displayed when a user\n"
"browses through all parts of the book.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:917
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advanced Handbook Features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:919
#, no-wrap
msgid "Global Values"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:923
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Sometimes, the same values are repeated many times in several parts of a\n"
"handbook. Global search and replace operations tend to forget some or introduce\n"
"unwanted changes. Besides, it can be useful to define different values to be\n"
"used in shared chapters depending on which handbook includes the chapter.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:930
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Global values can be defined in a handbook master file and used in all included\n"
"chapters.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:935
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To define global values, add a <c>&lt;values&gt;</c> element to the handbook\n"
"master file. Each value is then defined in a <c>&lt;key&gt;</c> element whose\n"
"<c>id</c> attribute identifies the value, i.e. it is the name of your variable.\n"
"The content of the <c>&lt;key&gt;</c> is its value.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:942
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following example defines three values in a handbook master file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:945
#, no-wrap
msgid "Define values in a handbook"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:946
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE book SYSTEM \"/dtd/book.dtd\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;!-- &#36;Header&#36; --&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;book&gt;\n"
"&lt;title&gt;Example Book Usage&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"\n"
"<i>&lt;values>\n"
" &lt;key id=\"arch\"&gt;x86&lt;/key&gt;\n"
" &lt;key id=\"min-cd-name\"&gt;install-x86-minimal-2007.0-r1.iso&lt;/key&gt;\n"
" &lt;key id=\"min-cd-size\"&gt;57&lt;/key&gt;\n"
"&lt;/values&gt;</i>\n"
"\n"
"&lt;author...&gt;\n"
"  ...\n"
"&lt;/author&gt;\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:967
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The defined values can then be used throughout the handbook with the in-line\n"
"<c>&lt;keyval id=\"key_id\"/&gt;</c> element. Specify the name of the key in its\n"
"<c>id</c> attribute, e.g. &lt;keyval id=\"min-cd-name\"/&gt; would be replaced by\n"
"\"install-x86-minimal-2007.0-r1.iso\" in our example.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:973
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using defined values"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:974
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;p&gt;\n"
"The Minimal Installation CD is called &lt;c&gt;<i>&lt;keyval id=\"min-cd-name\"/&gt;</i>&lt;/c&gt;\n"
"and takes up only <i>&lt;keyval id=\"min-cd-size\"/&gt;</i> MB of diskspace. You can use this\n"
"Installation CD to install Gentoo, but &lt;e&gt;only&lt;/e&gt; with a working Internet\n"
"connection.\n"
"&lt;/p&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:983
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To make life easier on our translators, only use actual values, i.e. content\n"
"that does not need to be translated. For instance, we defined the\n"
"<c>min-cd-size</c> value to <c>57</c> and not <c>57 MB</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:991
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conditional Elements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:995
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Chapters that are shared by several handbooks such as our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/\">Installation Handbooks</uri> often have small\n"
"differences depending on which handbook includes them. Instead of adding\n"
"content that is irrelevant to some handbooks, authors can add a condition to\n"
"the following elements: <c>&lt;section&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;subsection&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;body&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;note&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;impo&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;warn&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;pre&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;p&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;table&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;tr&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ul&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ol&gt;</c>\n"
"and <c>&lt;li&gt;</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1007
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The condition must be an <uri\n"
"link=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XPath\">XPATH</uri> expression that will be\n"
"evaluated when transforming the XML. If it evaluates to <c>true</c>, the\n"
"element is processed, if not, it is ignored. The condition is specified in a\n"
"<c>test</c> attribute.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1015
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The following example uses the <c>arch</c> value that is defined in each\n"
"handbook master file to condition some content:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1019
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using conditional elements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1020
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;body test=\"contains('AMD64 x86',func:keyval('arch'))\"&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;p&gt;\n"
"This paragraph applies to both x86 and AMD64 architectures.\n"
"&lt;/p&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;p test=\"func:keyval('arch')='x86'\"&gt;\n"
"This paragraph only applies to the x86 architecture.\n"
"&lt;/p&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;p test=\"func:keyval('arch')='AMD64'\"&gt;\n"
"This paragraph only applies to the AMD64 architecture.\n"
"&lt;/p&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;p test=\"func:keyval('arch')='PPC'\"&gt;\n"
"This paragraph will never be seen!\n"
"The whole body is skipped because of the first condition.\n"
"&lt;/p&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;/body&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;body test=\"contains('AMD64 PPC64',func:keyval('arch'))\"&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;p&gt;\n"
"This paragraph applies to the AMD64, PPC64 <comment>and PPC</comment> architectures because\n"
"the 'AMD64 PPC64' string does contain 'PPC'.\n"
"&lt;/p&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;note test=\"func:keyval('arch')='AMD64' or func:keyval('arch')='PPC64'\"&gt;\n"
"This note only applies to the AMD64 and PPC64 architectures.\n"
"&lt;/note&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;/body&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1060
#, no-wrap
msgid "Coding Style"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1062
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1066
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Since all Gentoo Documentation is a joint effort and several people will\n"
"most likely change existing documentation, a coding style is needed.\n"
"A coding style contains two sections. The first one is regarding\n"
"internal coding - how the XML-tags are placed. The second one is\n"
"regarding the content - how not to confuse the reader.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1074
#, no-wrap
msgid "Both sections are described next.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1080
#, no-wrap
msgid "Internal Coding Style"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1084
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>Newlines</b> must be placed immediately after <e>every</e>\n"
"GuideXML-tag (both opening as closing), except for:\n"
"<c>&lt;version&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;date&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;title&gt;</c>, \n"
"<c>&lt;th&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ti&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;li&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;i&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;e&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;uri&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;path&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;b&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;c&gt;</c>, \n"
"<c>&lt;comment&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;mail&gt;</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1094
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>Blank lines</b> must be placed immediately after <e>every</e>\n"
"<c>&lt;body&gt;</c> (opening tag only) and before <e>every</e>\n"
"<c>&lt;chapter&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;p&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;table&gt;</c>, \n"
"<c>&lt;author&gt;</c> (set), <c>&lt;pre&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ul&gt;</c>, \n"
"<c>&lt;ol&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;warn&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;note&gt;</c> and \n"
"<c>&lt;impo&gt;</c> (opening tags only).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>Word-wrapping</b> must be applied at 80 characters except inside\n"
"<c>&lt;pre&gt;</c>. You may only deviate from this rule when there is no other\n"
"choice (for instance when a URL exceeds the maximum amount of characters).  The\n"
"editor must then wrap whenever the first whitespace occurs. You should try to\n"
"keep the <e>rendered</e> content of <c>&lt;pre&gt;</c> elements within 80\n"
"columns to help console users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>Indentation</b> may not be used, except with the XML-constructs of which the\n"
"parent XML-tags are <c>&lt;tr&gt;</c> (from <c>&lt;table&gt;</c>),\n"
"<c>&lt;ul&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;ol&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;dl&gt;</c>, and\n"
"<c>&lt;author&gt;</c>. If indentation is used, it <e>must</e> be two spaces for\n"
"each indentation. That means <e>no tabs</e> and <e>not</e> more spaces.\n"
"Besides, tabs are not allowed in GuideXML documents.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In case word-wrapping happens in <c>&lt;ti&gt;</c>, <c>&lt;th&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;li&gt;</c> or <c>&lt;dd&gt;</c> constructs, indentation must be used for\n"
"the content.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1127
#, no-wrap
msgid "An example for indentation is:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1130
#, no-wrap
msgid "Indentation Example"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1131
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;table&gt;\n"
"&lt;tr&gt;\n"
"  &lt;th&gt;Foo&lt;/th&gt;\n"
"  &lt;th&gt;Bar&lt;/th&gt;\n"
"&lt;/tr&gt;\n"
"&lt;tr&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ti&gt;This is an example for indentation&lt;/ti&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ti&gt;\n"
"    In case text cannot be shown within an 80-character wide line, you\n"
"    must use indentation if the parent tag allows it\n"
"  &lt;/ti&gt;\n"
"&lt;/tr&gt;\n"
"&lt;/table&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;ul&gt;\n"
"  &lt;li&gt;First option&lt;/li&gt;\n"
"  &lt;li&gt;Second option&lt;/li&gt;\n"
"&lt;/ul&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>Attributes</b> may not have spaces in between the attribute, the \"=\" mark,\n"
"and the attribute value. As an example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1156
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attributes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Wrong  :</comment>     &lt;pre caption = \"Attributes\"&gt;\n"
"<comment>Correct:</comment>     &lt;pre caption=\"Attributes\"&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1164
#, no-wrap
msgid "External Coding Style"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside tables (<c>&lt;table&gt;</c>) and listings (<c>&lt;ul&gt;</c>,\n"
"<c>&lt;ol&gt;</c>) and <c>&lt;dl&gt;</c>, periods (\".\") should not be used\n"
"unless multiple sentences are used. In that case, every sentence should end\n"
"with a period (or other reading marks).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Every sentence, including those inside tables and listings, should start\n"
"with a capital letter.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xml-guide.xml:1179
#, no-wrap
